ow more child-centred disaster management, that recognises children's capacity to enhance disaster resilience, actually benefits at-risk communities as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aArenas, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArgyropoulos, Vassilios, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBingley, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCordani, Flaminia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelicado, Ana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelicado, Ana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGoto, Aya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrisi, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanari, Charikleia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeir, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLloyd Williams, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLópez Gómez, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMort, Maggie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMort, Maggie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNikolaraizi, Magda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPapazafiri, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRibeiro, Ana Sofia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel